|!Version |!Date |!Changes |
|0.1.27 |2026-04-08 |Add tw-gotchas/kin-filter: direction semantics, base inclusion, depth, global cache, field default, sort order |
|0.1.26 |2026-04-08 |Add wiki-based tests: ctx-match logic, path resolution, context-filtered visibility. Add test-edition for CI |
|0.1.25 |2026-04-07 |Add \define migration gotcha to tw-gotchas/wikitext, replace hardcoded border color with palette variable |
|0.1.24 |2026-04-07 |Add tw-gotchas/cascades (ViewTemplateBodyFilter ordering, third-party plugins breaking chain) and tw-gotchas/hooks (hook chain fragility, change event fallback, draft safety) |
|0.1.23 |2026-04-07 |Convert HTML heading to wikitext in settings page |
|0.1.22 |2026-04-02 |Help tree debug panel — shows full help page hierarchy with path/description/context per node. Toggle to show hidden (context-filtered) pages greyed out. Reads active context from chat |
|0.1.21 |2026-04-02 |Fix debug panel key display — use `$list` directly instead of `{{{ }}}` variable (first-result bug). Each key on its own line |
|0.1.20 |2026-04-02 |Help context debug panel — read-only view of active help context keys, registered via `$:/tags/rimir/llm-connect/debug-panel` tag. Appears in llm-connect's debug menu when llm-help is installed |
|0.1.19 |2026-04-01 |Add `tool-category: core` to llm_help tool for tree-based tool selector in llm-connect v0.1.43+ |
|0.1.12 |2026-03-30 |Add `[[` `]]` literal brackets gotcha to tw-gotchas/filters — brackets are filter syntax delimiters, must use variables |
|0.1.18 |2026-03-30 |Fix llm_help returning empty: root page detection used broken `get[field]is[blank]` pattern (use `_llm-help-root-page` function), context from chat never reached tool (add `__helpContext` fallback in `_llm-help-resolve-ctx`) |
|0.1.17 |2026-03-30 |Fix context popup: use `$click-outside` widget (stays open on checkbox toggle), move styling to stylesheet (fix transparent background from `<<colour>>` in inline styles) |
|0.1.16 |2026-03-30 |Context matching changed from exact to hierarchical prefix (`rimir/appify` matches `rimir/appify/channels`). Update docs: architecture, overview, faq, reference. Add browser state tiddlers to reference |
|0.1.15 |2026-03-30 |Settings browser: all contexts selected by default (fallback when state tiddler doesn't exist), Select all / Clear all at top of popup, visible/total page count |
|0.1.14 |2026-03-30 |Decouple settings browser from chat context — own state tiddler (`$:/state/rimir/llm-help/browser/context`), initializes with all contexts selected, Select all / Clear all buttons, visible/total page count |
|0.1.13 |2026-03-30 |Add filter gotcha #9: `subfilter`/`filter`/`reduce`/`map` cannot take literal filter operands with nested brackets — use `{tiddler}` or `<variable>` indirection |
|0.1.11 |2026-03-29 |Fix multi-context filtering: replace `search` substring match with proper set-intersection via helper function — multiple active contexts now work correctly |
|0.1.10 |2026-03-29 |Add conditional filter operators gotcha to tw-gotchas/filter-runs — build filter strings dynamically with $let instead of duplicating $list blocks |
|0.1.9 |2026-03-29 |Add nested {{{ }}} gotcha to tw-gotchas/wikitext — filter expressions cannot nest |
|0.1.8 |2026-03-29 |Add tw-gotchas/filter-runs page: ~ else semantics, + pipe vs union, :filter scope across runs, interleaving limitations |
|0.1.7 |2026-03-29 |Add tw-gotchas help pages: titles/brackets, filters, wikitext, shadows, slots — always available (no context) |
|0.1.6 |2026-03-29 |Add context selector popup in settings: toggle context keys via checkboxes with page counts, clear all button |
|0.1.5 |2026-03-28 |Fix context filtering: move empty-ctx guard into helper function to avoid run-prefix scoping issue |
|0.1.3 |2026-03-28 |Settings: always show active context value (displays "none" when unset) |
|0.1.2 |2026-03-28 |Switch active-context from `$:/config/` to `$:/temp/` — context is transient (resets on reload), not a permanent preference |
|0.1.1 |2026-03-28 |Fix filter functions: single-line \function pragmas, avoid :filter with negation operators, use :map for per-item segment extraction. Fix settings UI: inline actions for card navigation, HTML for block-level headings. Fix root page detection via !has[llm-help-path]. |
|0.1.0 |2026-03-27 |Initial release: core help system with llm_help tool, help browser UI, user shortcuts |
